{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he spake a parable unto them to this end, that men ought always to pray, and not to faint;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Saying,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "speaker": "The Lord"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 9,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he spake this parable unto certain which trusted in themselves that they were righteous, and despised others:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And they brought unto him also infants, that he would touch them: but when his disciples saw it, they rebuked them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But Jesus called them unto him, and said,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 18,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Good Master, what shall I do to inherit eternal life?",
          "speaker": "A certain ruler"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 19,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Jesus said unto him,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "All these have I kept from my youth up.",
          "speaker": "The ruler"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Now when Jesus heard these things, he said unto him,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when Jesus saw that he was very sorrowful, he said,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 26,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Who then can be saved?",
          "speaker": "Those who heard"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 27,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he said,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 28,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Lo, we have left all, and followed thee.",
          "speaker": "Peter"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 29,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he said unto them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 31,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then he took unto him the twelve, and said unto them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        ""
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 35,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And it came to pass, that as he was come nigh unto Jericho, a certain blind man sat by the way side begging:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        ""
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 38,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Jesus, thou Son of David, have mercy on me.",
          "speaker": "Blind man"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 39,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Thou Son of David, have mercy on me.",
          "speaker": "Blind man"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 40,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Jesus stood, and commanded him to be brought unto him: and when he was come near, he asked him,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 41,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Saying,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Lord, that I may receive my sight.",
          "speaker": "Blind man"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 42,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Jesus said unto him,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    }
  ]
}